The task of tranquillizing and preparing their minds devolves upon the jugglerS‚ who, whenever any thing is to be feared, or any thing to be done, consult the evil spirit. About the beginning of the night a company of old women assemble in a huge tent. The mistress of the band, an old woman remarkable for wrinkles and grey hairs, strikes every now and then two large discordant drums, at intervals of four sounds, and whilst these instruments return a horrible bellowing‚ she, with a harsh voice, mutters kinds of songs, like a person mourning.
